commit.message:
Fix missing check for whitespace at the current +2 for germanic 'C'.
(This changes the outcome of 'ach' to 'AK' from ['AX','AK'])

Change padding to space to allow testing for whitespace to work
correctly.

Changed name back to metaphone.

This is in preparation for a new release on PyPI which will point to the original metaphone (and not metafone) project.

Merge pull request #4 from ThijsMergaert/master

Use io.open in setup.py to specify UTF-8 encoding

Thanks for the change, @ThijsMergaert!
Use io.open in setup.py to specify UTF-8 encoding

Changed the tag line

Github shows that this is a fork, and the "about" section of the README mentions it's a fork; better to describe what the project actually is.

Various useful changes.
